"title": "6252: temptation, and Jesus Christ",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "6252: temptation, and jesus christ",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Jesus Christ, like every other human being, knew temptation. However, he never yielded to it. The sinlessness of Christ refers to his obedient refusal to give in to temptation. It does not mean that he did not experience temptation himself.</p>\n<h2>The temptation of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark1:13\">MRK 1:13</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt4:1-Matt4:10\">MAT 4:1–4:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke4:1-Luke4:13\">LUK 4:1–4:13</a></p>\n<h2>The temptation to avoid the cross</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:21-Matt16:23\">MAT 16:21–16:23</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark8:31-Mark8:33\">MRK 8:31–8:33</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt26:36-Matt26:44\">MAT 26:36–26:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark14:32-Mark14:42\">MRK 14:32–14:42</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:40-Luke22:46\">LUK 22:40–22:46</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt27:39-Matt27:44\">MAT 27:39–27:44</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark15:31-Mark15:32\">MRK 15:31–15:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:36-Luke23:37\">LUK 23:36–23:37</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke23:39\">LUK 23:39</a></p>\n<h2>The temptation to please the crowd</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:16\">LUK 11:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt12:38-Matt12:39\">MAT 12:38–12:39</a> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke11:29\">LUK 11:29</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:18\">JHN 2:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John6:30\">JHN 6:30</a></p>\n<h2>The significance of the temptation of Jesus Christ</h2>\n<h3>Believers can identify with Jesus Christ in his temptation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:18\">HEB 2:18</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Believers can have confidence in the face of temptation</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb4:15-Heb4:16\">HEB 4:15–4:16</a></strong></p>",
